President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed April 9, 2022, as National Former Prisoner of War Recognition Day. This day honors the courage and sacrifice of the tens of thousands of American and Filipino prisoners of war who endured the Bataan Death March and the more than half a million service members who became prisoners of war throughout history. Former prisoners of war are recognized as some of the bravest individuals in the nation, demonstrating incredible personal courage, love of country, and devotion to duty. The proclamation calls upon Americans and government officials to observe this day by honoring the service and sacrifice of all former prisoners of war and expressing eternal gratitude for their sacrifices.